Class LOP

  • java.lang.Object
    • semanticMarkup.io.input.lib.taxonx.LOP
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    And, AndNot, Or, OrNot

    public class LOP
extends java.lang.Object
    The logical operator defined type. An LOP can contain 2 of either COPs or LOPs (i.e. LOPs can be nested).

    Java class for LOP complex type.

      • getCOPOrLOP

        public java.util.List<javax.xml.bind.JAXBElement<?>> getCOPOrLOP()
        Gets the value of the copOrLOP property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the copOrLOP property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getCOPOrLOP().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<COP> JAXBElement<LessThanOrEquals> JAXBElement<LOP> JAXBElement<Equals> JAXBElement<And> JAXBElement<Or> JAXBElement<Like> JAXBElement<AndNot> JAXBElement<GreaterThan> JAXBElement<LessThan> JAXBElement<GreaterThanOrEquals> JAXBElement<NotEquals> JAXBElement<In> JAXBElement<OrNot>
